Learning Objectives:


By the end of this module, students will be able to:

  • Understand and apply the basic principles of design (e.g., balance, contrast, emphasis, unity, etc.).
  • Analyze how these principles function in real-world examples.
  • Create a basic composition incorporating at least three principles of design.

props.text: What Are the Principles of Design?

Video Lecture (10 minutes):

    • Definition and importance of design principles.
    • Overview of the principles:
      • Balance: Symmetrical, asymmetrical, radial.
      • Contrast: Use of light/dark, textures, colors.
      • Emphasis: Highlighting focal points.
      • Unity and Harmony: Creating a cohesive design.
      • Movement and Rhythm: Guiding the viewer's eye.
      • Proportion and Scale: Relationships between elements.

props.text: Applying Principles in Composition

Case Study (15 minutes):

      • Explore famous designs (e.g., magazine covers, logos, art pieces).
      • Analyze how principles are used effectively.
      • Quiz: Identify the primary principle in each example.

    • Demonstration Video (10 minutes):

      • Walkthrough: Designing a balanced and unified composition.

    • Hands-On Exercise (30 minutes):

      • Create a simple poster using provided assets.
      • Use at least three design principles.
